In [459]:
#    (year, month, quarter)
trd_tot$orr_dt = ymd(trd_tot$orr_dt) # Year-Month-Day
trd_tot$trd_year = year(trd_tot$orr_dt)
trd_tot$trd_month = month(trd_tot$orr_dt)
trd_tot$trd_quarter= quarter(trd_tot$orr_dt) # Quarter ()
trd_tot$trd_ym = trd_tot$trd_year*100 + trd_tot$trd_month # YYYYMM
trd_tot$trd_yQ = trd_tot$trd_year*100 + trd_tot$trd_quarter # YYYYQQ

act_info$opn_year = floor((act_info$act_opn_ym)/100) # YYYY
act_info$opn_month = act_info$act_opn_ym - (act_info$opn_year)*100 # MM
act_info$opn_quarter = ifelse(act_info$opn_month == 0, 0,
                              ifelse(act_info$opn_month < 4, 1,
                                     ifelse(act_info$opn_month < 7, 2,
                                            ifelse(act_info$opn_month < 10, 3, 4)
                                     )
                              )
) # QQ
act_info$opn_yQ = (act_info$opn_year)*100 + act_info$opn_quarter # YYYYQQ

trd_age_table <- trd_tot %>% filter(age_group != 'B' & trd_year == 2019) %>%
  group_by(age_group) %>%
  summarise(cus_n = n_distinct(cus_id)) %>% data.frame() %>%
  arrange(desc('age_group')) %>%
  mutate(per = round(100*(cus_n/sum(cus_n)),1)) %>%
  mutate(ypos = cumsum(per) - 0.5*per)

a <- ggplot(trd_age_table, aes(x="", y=per, fill = age_group )) + 
  geom_bar(width = 1, stat='identity', color = 'white') +

  ggtitle('2019     ') +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(family = "serif", face = "bold", hjust = 0.5, size = 15, color = "black"),
        text =element_text(face = "bold"))

for (i in grade){

      filter(tco_cus_grd_cd == i & trd_yQ == 202001)

    unique_id <- unique(cus$cus_id)

cus_final_freq <- data.frame()

for (i in unique(trd_tot_yz20$cus_id)){   # 3276
  
  df <- trd_tot_yz20 %>% filter(cus_id == i)  #    filter
  
  min_month <- min(df$trd_month)  #      mm
  min_day <- min(as.Date(df$orr_dt))  #    yyyy-mm-dd
  day_diff <- unclass(as.Date('2020-07-01') - min_day )[[1]] #   ~ 2020-07-01  
  
  
  k=0
  
  for (j in 1:6){
    
    df_j <- df %>% filter(trd_month == j)  #   
    if (nrow(df_j) != 0){
      k = k+1
    }
  }     # +    ? ==> k
  
  trd_freq <- nrow(df)  #   ==>   ?
  sell_freq <- nrow(df[df$sby_dit_cd == 1,])  #    ===>   ?
  buy_freq <- nrow(df[df$sby_dit_cd == 2,])  #    ===>   ?
  
  unique_day <- n_distinct(df$orr_dt)  #    ==>   ?
  
  
  dfdf <- data.frame(cus_id = i , 
                     freq_mean_month = trd_freq / k ,  #     (+)
                     freq_mean_day = trd_freq / unique_day, #     (+)
                     freq_max_mean_day = (max(sell_freq,buy_freq,na.rm = T)) / unique_day, # max(,) /  
                     freq_day_month_ratio = unique_day / k, #    
                     freq_day_minmonth_ratio = unique_day / (7-min_month), 
                     freq_day_ratio = unique_day / day_diff)  # (~2020-07-01)  ?
  
  cus_final_freq <- rbind(cus_final_freq, dfdf)

}

cus_final_scale <- data.frame()

suppressMessages(for (i in unique(trd_tot_yz20$cus_id)){   # 3276
  
  df <- trd_tot_yz20 %>% filter(cus_id == i)
  df_sell <- trd_tot_yz20 %>% filter(cus_id == i & sby_dit_cd ==1)
  df_buy <- trd_tot_yz20 %>% filter(cus_id == i & sby_dit_cd ==2)
  
  k=0  # 
  kk=0  #  
  
  for (j in 1:6){
    
    # j    (/)
    
    df_j_sell <- df_sell %>% filter(trd_month == j) 
    df_j_buy <- df_buy %>% filter(trd_month == j)  
    
    if (nrow(df_j_sell) != 0){
      k = k+1  }    ## k  ==> 6      

    if (nrow(df_j_buy) != 0) {
      kk = kk+1   ## kk  ==> 6      
    }
  }
   
  
  ### 1  ### 
  # 1      
  max_totpr <- max(df$tot_pr)
  
  ### 2  ###
  #  1   /  max 
  mean_1freq_totpr <- df %>% group_by(sby_dit_cd) %>% summarise(mean2 = mean(tot_pr)) %>% 
    select(mean2) %>% max()
  
   
  ### 3  ### 
  # ()  /   max
  mean_month_totpr <- max( sum(df_buy$tot_pr)/kk , sum(df_sell$tot_pr)/k , na.rm = T )
  
  
  ### 4  ###  
  #  /   ==>   ==>       max 
  mean_sby_iem_totpr <- df %>% group_by(sby_dit_cd,iem_cd) %>% summarise(mean1 = mean(tot_pr))
  
  mean_iem_totpr_df <-  aggregate(mean1~sby_dit_cd,mean_sby_iem_totpr,mean)
  mean_iem_totpr <- max(mean_iem_totpr_df$mean1)  ## max(,)

  cus_scale_df <- data.frame(cus_id = i,
                             max_totpr = max_totpr, 
                             mean_1freq_totpr = mean_1freq_totpr,
                             mean_month_totpr = mean_month_totpr,
                             mean_iem_totpr = mean_iem_totpr)
  
  cus_final_scale <- rbind(cus_final_scale, cus_scale_df)
  
})

프로파일끼리 4개의 Factor (F, A, R, M)간의 차이가 서로 유의한지 검정¶

Krusckal test를 통해 유의하다는 것을 확인¶

In [600]:
#   FARM     

col_name <- colnames(df_score)[1:4]
aov_result_df <- data.frame()

for (i in col_name){
  
  bar_data <- bartlett.test(eval(parse(text=i)) ~ cluster, data = df_score)
  bar_pvalue <- bar_data$p.value
  
  if(bar_pvalue < 0.05){
    
    krus_data <- kruskal.test(eval(parse(text=i)) ~ cluster, data = df_score)
    krus_pvalue <- krus_data$p.value
    
    krus_result <- ifelse(krus_pvalue < 0.05 , '','')
    aov_result <- ''
    
    p_value <- krus_pvalue
  } else {
    
    aov_data <- aov(eval(parse(text=i)) ~ cluster, data = df_score)
    aov_result <- summary(aov_data)
    aov_pvalue <- unlist(aov_result)[[9]]
    
    aov_result <- ifelse(aov_pvalue < 0.05 , '','')
    krus_result <- ''
    
    p_value <- aov_pvalue
  }
  
  aov_df <- data.frame(colname = i,
                       p_value = p_value,
                       aov_result = aov_result,
                       krus_result = krus_result)
  
  aov_result_df <- rbind(aov_result_df, aov_df)
  
}

  kosdaq200_kosdaq_ratio <- kosdaq200_num / kosdaq_num ###### 2020    200 
  
  max_orrpr <- max(cus_i_df[, orr_pr])  ##### 2020     (1)
  min_orrpr <- min(cus_i_df[, orr_pr])  ##### 2020     (1)
  
  mean_orrpr_1 <- cus_i_df %>% group_by(iem_cd) %>% summarise(mean_orrpr = mean(orr_pr))
  mean_orrpr <- mean(mean_orrpr_1$mean_orrpr) ###### 2020    (iem )
  
  
  #############################   ##################################
  cus_i_df_oss <- cus_i_df %>% filter(country == 'oss')  # i   filter
  cus_i_df_kr <- cus_i_df %>% filter(country == 'kr')  # i   filter
  
  oss_num <- n_distinct(cus_i_df_oss$iem_cd)  # i  2020   
  kr_num <- n_distinct(cus_i_df_kr$iem_cd)  # i  2020   
  
  if (oss_num == 0){  
    oss_trd <- 0 
  } else {
    oss_trd <- 1   #     1,  0  
  }
  
  kr_oss_iem_ratio <- kr_num / (oss_num + kr_num)  # 2020     
  kr_oss_freq_ratio <- nrow(cus_i_df_kr) / nrow(cus_i_df)  #        
  kr_oss_totpr_ratio <- sum(cus_i_df_kr$tot_pr) / sum(cus_i_df$tot_pr) #       
  
  
  #######################   (+-) ###############################
   #       
  income_ratio <- sum(cus_i_df[cus_i_df$sby_dit_cd==1,tot_pr]) / sum(cus_i_df$tot_pr) 
   #   -  
  income_totpr <- sum(cus_i_df[cus_i_df$sby_dit_cd==1,tot_pr]) - sum(cus_i_df[cus_i_df$sby_dit_cd==2,tot_pr])
  
  
  #####################     ####################################
  cus_act_id <- act_info %>% filter(cus_id == i) %>% select(act_id) #    
  act_num <- nrow(cus_act_id)  #######    
  act_trd_num <-  n_distinct(cus_i_df$act_id)  #  
  trd_act_ratio <- act_trd_num / act_num  ######        
  
  
  #######################   #############################################
  buy_qty_ratio <- sum(cus_i_df[cus_i_df$sby_dit_cd==2,cns_qty]) / sum(cus_i_df$cns_qty)
 
  qty_sum <- aggregate(cns_qty ~ iem_cd, cus_i_df, sum)  #  (,)  
  
  if (nrow(cus_i_df[sby_dit_cd == 2,]) != 0){
  qty_buy_sum <- aggregate(cns_qty ~ iem_cd, cus_i_df[sby_dit_cd == 2,] , sum)  #  ()  
  colnames(qty_buy_sum) <- c('iem_cd', 'buy_cns_qty')
  
  qty_df <- left_join(qty_sum, qty_buy_sum,by = 'iem_cd') %>% mutate(iem_buy_qty_ratio = buy_cns_qty /cns_qty)
  qty_df$iem_buy_qty_ratio[which(is.na(qty_df$iem_buy_qty_ratio))] <- 0
  
  iem_buy_qty_ratio_mean <- mean(qty_df$iem_buy_qty_ratio)   #  (/(+))  
  
  } else {
    iem_buy_qty_ratio_mean <- 0
  }#  (  /(+))   
  
  freq_sum <- cus_i_df %>% group_by(iem_cd) %>% summarise(freq = n())  #     (+)
  freq_buy_sum <- cus_i_df %>% filter(sby_dit_cd == 2) %>% group_by(iem_cd) %>% summarise(buy_freq = n())  #     
  freq_sum_df <- left_join(freq_sum, freq_buy_sum, by='iem_cd') %>% mutate(iem_buy_freq_ratio = buy_freq / freq)
  freq_sum_df$iem_buy_freq_ratio[which(is.na(freq_sum_df$iem_buy_freq_ratio))] <- 0
  
  iem_buy_freq_ratio_mean <- mean(freq_sum_df$iem_buy_freq_ratio) #  (/(+))   
  
  
  #######################   () #############################################
  buy_iem_mean_df <- cus_i_df %>% filter(sby_dit_cd == 2 ) %>% group_by(iem_cd) %>% summarise(buy_mean_totpr = mean(tot_pr))
  
  iem_buy_mean_totpr_range <- with(buy_iem_mean_df, max(buy_mean_totpr) - min(buy_mean_totpr)) 
  iem_buy_totpr_CV <- sd(buy_iem_mean_df$buy_mean_totpr) / mean(buy_iem_mean_df$buy_mean_totpr) 
  
  if (sum(unique_trd_iem %in% 'A005930') == 0){
    samsung <- 0
  } else {
    samsung <- 1
  }  #     1,  0  

  cus_yq_df <- data.frame(cus_id = i,
                          iem_tot_num = iem_tot_num,  
                          kospi_ratio = kospi_ratio,
                          kosdaq_ratio = kosdaq_ratio,
                          kospi200_ratio = kospi200_ratio,
                          kosdaq200_ratio = kosdaq200_ratio,
                          kospi200_kospi_ratio = kospi200_kospi_ratio,
                          kosdaq200_kosdaq_ratio = kosdaq200_kosdaq_ratio,
                          max_orrpr = max_orrpr,
                          min_orrpr = min_orrpr,
                          mean_orrpr = mean_orrpr,
                          
                          oss_trd = oss_trd,
                          kr_oss_iem_ratio = kr_oss_iem_ratio,
                          kr_oss_freq_ratio = kr_oss_freq_ratio,
                          kr_oss_totpr_ratio = kr_oss_totpr_ratio,
                          
                          income_ratio = income_ratio,
                          income_totpr = income_totpr,
                          
                          act_num = act_num,
                          trd_act_ratio = trd_act_ratio,
                          
                          buy_qty_ratio = buy_qty_ratio,
                          iem_buy_qty_ratio_mean = iem_buy_qty_ratio_mean,
                          iem_buy_freq_ratio_mean = iem_buy_freq_ratio_mean,
                          
                          iem_buy_mean_totpr_range = iem_buy_mean_totpr_range,
                          iem_buy_totpr_CV = iem_buy_totpr_CV,
                          
                          samsung = samsung
                          )
  
  final_df <- rbind(final_df, cus_yq_df)
  
}

# "" Bartlett  .
##  --> ANOVA
##  -->Kruskal


###  bartlett 
## H0 : . 
## H1 : . 
## p-value < 0.05  H0 ===> kruskal   

## ANOVA or Kruskal   
## H0 :    
## H1 :    .
## p-value < 0.05  H0 ===>  . 

col_name <- colnames(final_df)[c(2:11,13:24)]

aov_result_df <- data.frame()

for (i in col_name){
  
  bar_data <- bartlett.test(eval(parse(text=i)) ~ cluster, data = final_df)
  bar_pvalue <- bar_data$p.value
  
  if(bar_pvalue < 0.05){
    
  krus_data <- kruskal.test(eval(parse(text=i)) ~ cluster, data = final_df)
  krus_pvalue <- krus_data$p.value
  
  krus_result <- ifelse(krus_pvalue < 0.05 , '','')
  aov_result <- ''
  
  p_value <- krus_pvalue
  } else {
  
  aov_data <- aov(eval(parse(text=i)) ~ cluster, data = final_df)
  aov_result <- summary(aov_data)
  aov_pvalue <- unlist(aov_result)[[9]]
  
  aov_result <- ifelse(aov_pvalue < 0.05 , '','')
  krus_result <- ''
  
  p_value <- aov_pvalue
  }
  
  aov_df <- data.frame(colname = i,
                       p_value = p_value,
                       ANOVA_result = aov_result,
                       Kruskal_test_result = krus_result)
  
  aov_result_df <- rbind(aov_result_df, aov_df)
  
}

4. Conclusion (결론)¶

4.1 Implication (시사점)¶

1. 해외 투자 경험 유무에 상관없이 프로파일의 분포 비율은 비슷하다.¶

      .

2. Y&Z세대 대부분의 투자자들의 수익은 제로섬 (zero-sum)이다.¶

    .      .  .

3. Y&Z세대 대부분의 투자자들은 많은 종목을 경험해보지 않았다.¶

      .

4. 주식을 '자주', '꾸준히' 투자를 하는 고객군이 수익 편차가 작다.¶

    ,    .

5. 최근에 소액 매수하는 간헐적 주기의 투자자는 코스닥 상위 200종목에는 투자를 잘 하지 않는다.¶

   200    . (   200 vs   200 X)
     .
